sentences: Rhiannon Afua "Rhian" Benson (born 10 January 1977 in Accra, Ghana) is a Ghanaian-British soul and jazz singer and songwriter.
Benson moved to Los Angeles, California to record her debut album, Gold Coast, which was released in October 2003.
Benson won a Mobo Award in 2005.
With the help of Denmark's production duo, Jonas Rendbo and Daniel Fridell, Benson released her second album, Hands Clean, on 14 February 2011.
"Better Without You" was the first single to be released in February 2011.
